betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§7§oThe interface has two functions, see the section on network I/O for an explanation on the other functionality.

The slots at the bottom on an interface GUI can be used to store patterns. Each pattern encodes a recipe or processing step.

If the interface is touching a molecular assembler, it will perform a crafting recipe.

If the interface is next to a machine (furnace, pulverizer, chest, etc) it will perform a processing recipe.

Some machines don't auto output, so you will have to use conduits or other transfer pipes to put machine outputs back into the interface.
